# Singly Linked List Implementation (Java)

This project contains a complete implementation of a Singly Linked List in Java.

It covers fundamental operations required for understanding Linked List concepts.

-----

### Insertion Operations
- Insert at Beginning
- Insert at End
- Insert at Specific Position

### Deletion Operations
- Delete from Beginning
- Delete from End
- Delete at Specific Position

### Utility Operations
- Count number of nodes
- Search for a value
- Reverse the linked list (iterative)
- Find middle node using Slow & Fast Pointer
- Display list

-----

## Concepts Used

- Pointer manipulation
- Iterative traversal
- Two-pointer technique (slow & fast pointer)
- In-place reversal
- Edge case handling

-----

